<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Directors of 8 Financial Organizations Punished </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The directors of eight financial
organizations have been punished for illegal operations.
</P>
<P>
Demerits were recorded in their work records, and some were
dismissed from their posts.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, at a
teleconference held here today, called on financial organizations
nationwide to do a good job of financial work, and to strictly
punish those who engage in activities which violate related
regulations and laws.
</P>
<P>
Dai stressed that financial organizations must crack down on
illegal financial activities, such as attracting deposits with
artificially high interest rates, keeping disorderly accounts,
poor cash management, the issuing of long-term credit
certificates, the diversion of state funds into personal accounts
and violation of the foreign currency regulations.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that strict punishment for illegal financial
activities and the strengthening of self-monitoring systems will
help the country develop a safe and sound financial order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
