<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Bolivia Quake Rises to 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The death toll in Friday's
powerful earthquake in central Bolivia rose to 18, reports
reaching here from La Paz said.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said about 100 were missing.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, measured 6.8 on the open-ended Richter scale,
centred on the towns of Aiquile and Totora, 400 kilometers east of
La Paz.
</P>
<P>
Sixteem people were killed in the town of Aiquile and two in
Totora, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Bolivian President Hugo Banzer rushed to the disaster zone to
direct rescue operations and asked the population for calm.
</P>
</TEXT>
