<HEADLINE> Zou Jiahua on Environmental Inspection Tour of Hainan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) began
an marine environmental inspection tour of south China's island
province of Hainan today.
</P>
<P>
The inspection team, headed by Zou, will check up the situation
of the marine environmental pollution in Hainan and the
supervision on the marine resources protection.
</P>
<P>
With two million sq km sea accounting two-third of the
country's total, Hainan has set up 40 law enforcement
organizations with 635 officials in the field who have handled
punishment on 130 marine pollution cases with 426,000 yuan fine,
registered 200 enterprises about their pollution statistics, and
set up 13 marine nature reserves.  
</P>
</TEXT>
