<HEADLINE> Zulle Wins Stage to Return Overall Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Swiss rider Alex Zulle won his second
stage victory of the Tour of Italy and wrested back the overall
lead as the race reached Laceno of Italy on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Zulle, hold the overall lead through the first three days after
winning the prologue in Nice, surged ahead from the final
kilometers of the sixth stage, a tough 158-km mountain run from
Maddaloni.
</P>
<P>
Overnight race leader Michele Bartoli finished second,
fractionally ahead of his breakaway companions Luc Leblanc of
France and popular Italian Marco Pantani, who were all 24 seconds
behind Zulle.
</P>
<P>
Zulle, a time trial specialist with the Festina team, took
advantage of the closing kilometres on the flat, as the route
wound around Lake Laceno here in southwest Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
