<HEADLINE> Duma Postpones Debate on Partnership Treaty with Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma, or the lower
house of parliament, decided to postpone its debate on the
ratification of a Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and
Partnership with the Ukraine until June.
</P>
<P>
Duma Chairman Gennady Seleznev said on Friday he had sent a
letter to his Ukrainian counterpart and asked for an explanation
of Ukraine's position on the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO).
</P>
<P>
Recently, Ukranian Foreign Minister Boris Tarasyuk made some
comments on the Ukraine-NATO cooperation, suggesting that Ukraine
does not rule out the possibility of joining the Western military
bloc.
</P>
<P>
The Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Partnership was
signed on May 31, 1997 when Russian President Boris Yeltsin paid a
visit to Ukraine. 
</P>
