<HEADLINE> Lebanon to Hold Arab Food Industry Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon is to hold the Arab Food
Industry Conference and Arab Food International Fair from June 25
to 30, it was announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 Arab companies specialized in food and package sector
will attend the meeting and exhibit their latest products in the
fair, said Abu Ziky, president of Lebanese Economic and Trade
Association, the organizer of the conference.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the meeting, to be inaugurated by Lebanese
Prime Minister Rafik Hariri, will focus on the current food and
package industries in the Arab world and their prospects.
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss the difficulties the Arab food industry
is meeting in light of regional and international changes and
requirements from international quality systems, Ziky said.
</P>
<P>
He added that issues such as ways to finance food industries,
activate Arab food imports and boost trade cooperation, are also
on the agenda of a series of sessions.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Industry Minister Nadim Salem stressed the importance
of the food industry to the Arab world, saying the growth of food
production lags behind that of population.
</P>
<P>
He said that food consumption rose by an annually 7 percent in
the past two decades in the Arab world, due to increases in
population, incomes and living standards, compared to the 2
percent growth in food production.
</P>
<P>
He called for closer cooperation among Arab countries in this
sector in an effort to face the challenges of economic
globalization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
