<HEADLINE> Train Accident Kills 17 in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 passengers
were killed and hundreds injured in a tragic train accident
Friday morning in Malawi's southern Thyolo District, about 40 Km
east of commercial city of Blantyre.
</P>
<P>
The train which left Blantyre's Limbe station at 5 a.m.
derailed due to "a faulty breaking system" as it negotiated a
bend at Lunda on its way to a southern-most Nsanje District close
to Mozambican border.
</P>
<P>
Seventeen dead bodies were recovered as well as many
casualties retrieved when Malawi railways official and medical
personnel arrived at the scene at about 10 a.m., reported the Malawi
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Some eye witnesses said about 100 casualties were taken to
Blantyre's Queen Elizabeth Central Hospital by 8 a.m.
</P>
<P>
However, some sources said the train was overloaded and that
the engine was not fit to travel as it had a mechanical problem.
</P>
<P>
The number of dead bodies is expected to rise as many bodies
were still trapped beneath the wagons as efforts to retrieve them
were underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
