<HEADLINE> France to Extradite Basque Militant to Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- France will extradite a militant of
the Basque independence movement ETA to Spain after she has
finished her prison term in France.
</P>
<P>
The prefectural government of Pas-de-Calais in northern France
made the decision to extradite Idoia Lopez Riano, nicknamed
Tigress, wanted by the Spanish authorities for suspected
involvement in 23 assassinations, most of them committed in 1986
in Madrid.
</P>
<P>
She was arrested in 1994 in southern France and condemned to
five years in prison in 1996 for associations with criminals and
illegally bearing arms prohibited in France.
</P>
<P>
But her prison sentence was shortened and she was originally
due to be released Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A committee in charge of extradition in Pas-de-Calais
considered the presence of Tigress in France "a threat" to public
security because of her violent behaviors.
</P>
<P>
The Socialist government of France has promised Spain that it
will fully cooperate in fighting ETA militants taking shelter in
France, especially its southwest Basque region bordering Spain.
</P>
</TEXT>
