<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Lumberman Gets U.N. Environmental Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- An 84-year-old lumberman, who has
planted thousands of trees in northeastern China to "pay back his
debt to nature," has won the 1998 U.N. environmental award, the
U.N. Environment Program (UNEP) announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 23 individuals and organizations from 19 countries
are to receive the U.N. Global 500 Roll award at World
Environment Day celebrations in Moscow on June 5, said UNEP chief
Klaus Topfer.
</P>
<P>
Yongshun Ma, living in densely forested Heilongjiang Province,
had cut down hundreds of thousands of trees during his 21-year
career as a lumberman before retiring in 1982.
</P>
<P>
Witnessing the mounting environmental degradation around, Ma
felt guilty and reproached his overlogging. Therefore, he
decided to devote his remaining life to environmental protection
by planting 36,500 trees as "atonement".
</P>
<P>
In 1991, when he turned 78 and there were some 1,000 trees
left to meet the target, Ma convinced all of his family -- 16
people spanning three generations -- to plant trees on holidays.
At the end of that spring, all his "debt" was paid finally.
</P>
<P>
However, Ma has been continuing his new life. By 1996, he had
planted 40,000 trees and built a high-qualified breeding base for
trees.
</P>
<P>
Motivated by Ma's action, more and more people in the region
are planting trees and the forest there is expanding at a record
speed.
</P>
<P>
Ma has also taught a lot of people how to breed and plant
trees successfully. Tree planting efforts under his guidance win
a success rate of 95 percent.
</P>
<P>
Ma, together with other U.N. environmental award winners, sets
up example which "will inspire and guide many other men, women
and young people to join the global coalition dedicated to
protecting the environment," said Topfer.
</P>
<P>
Some 664 individuals and organizations, in both the adult and
youth categories, have been honored since UNEP launched the
Global 500 award in 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
