<HEADLINE> Turkey Rejects Greek Speaker's Accusations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkey on Friday dismissed as
"baseless" recent allegations made by Greek Parliament Speaker
Apostholos Kaklamanis over the killing of Pontus Greeks 79 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by Turkish Foreign Ministry Friday said that
"Kaklamanis' remarks are completely baseless. The historically
incorrect claims about massacre of Pontus Greeks have been
fabricated in order to charge Turkey with baseless accusations".
</P>
<P>
"We regret the fact that such baseless remarks were delivered
by the Greek parliament speaker. We condemn his statements which
serve nothing but to fan hostility against Turkey," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Kaklamanis has accused Turkey of carrying out an ethnic
cleansing campaign against Pontus Greeks living in the country's
Black Sea region in 1919.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Greece, both members of the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization, have long been at odds over control of the Aegean's
airspace, waters, mineral rights and the divided island of
Cyprus. 
</P>
