<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8,500 Vietnamese Fall Victim to HIV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 23 (Xinhua) -- 8,500 Vietnamese were found to be
infected with the HIV virus, a virus which is responsible for
AIDS, the Vietnam News reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However, the actual number of HIV-infected people is six to ten
times higher than the number of cases detected, the
English-language daily added.
</P>
<P>
Of those affected, 90 percent are under 30 and adolescents
account for five percent.
</P>
<P>
Free-lance, jobless people, street children, prostitutes and
drug users are listed as high risk aids infected groups, said the
paper.
</P>
<P>
It is also extremely difficult to provide them with the
necessary information about the virus in order to raise their
awareness of the disease.
</P>
<P>
A nationwide year-long campaign was launched on Friday by the
joint United Nations program on HIV AIDS (UNAIDS).
</P>
<P>
The campaign hopes to attract more young people and to inform
them on HIV prevention and care efforts, to enhance their
awareness of the devastating impact of HIV on youth, and to
promote support for young people in their fight against AIDS.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
