<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Win Uber Cup Badminton Finals for Sixth Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Runners-up China ensured a record
sixth Uber Cup Finals victory after they scored an unscalable 3-0
lead over defending champions Indonesia in the 17th world women's
team championships final here Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
It was a successful comeback for China, which, after five
consecutive wins from 1984 to 1992, had finished runners-up to
Indonesia in the past two championships.
</P>
<P>
China's world number three Gong Zhichao, 20, was the player of
the day as she won over 10th-ranked Indonesian Mia Audina 9-11,
12-10, 11-4 in the second singles and the third match of the final
in one hour and 17 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Indonesian had beaten Gong twice in their three
previous meetings since December 1996.
</P>
<P>
Audina, Olympic silver-medalist from the Atlanta Games, came
from behind at 4-6 to win the first game 11-9. Gong returned
strongly to take the second after lagging behind 7-10, with superb
volleys and drops.
</P>
<P>
Numerous errors cost Audina badly in the decisive rubber, which
helped Gong lead throughout the game to a 11-4 win.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Saturday evening, China's world number one Ye Zhaoying
defeated world number seven Susi Susanti 11-9, 10-12, 11-5 in the
opening singles match and top-ranked Chinese doubles pair Ge Fei
and Gu Jun downed Indonesians Rosiana Zelin and Indarti Isoliana
15-7, 15-1 in the following doubles.
</P>
<P>
At press time, the two teams are still engaged in the two
remaining matches -- a doubles and a singles, although their
results would in no way affect the Chinese victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
