<P>
COLOMBO, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga Saturday urged leaders of all political parties to
pave the way for their supporters to restore peace in the country.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national convention of the Sri Lankan Muslim
Congress here, Kumaratunga said the political leaders should
shoulder a great responsibility for changing the path of the
nation when it is facing a decisive moment.
</P>
<P>
Terrorism in the north should be defeated and all political
parties join hands to protect democracy and peace.
</P>
<P>
She said the destruction of human lives should not be allowed
for political games.
</P>
<P>
The president reiterated that the responsibility of the
government and the opposition is to protect the lives of the
people.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has long been plagued by problems between the
Sinhalese and Tamil-- the major ethnic groups in the country.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the government
for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the island
country since 1983. More than 55,000 people have been reportedly
killed in the war.
</P>
<P>
The president also said the only solution to the ethnic
conflict is a political one and that all should act as one Sri
Lankan nation for a new era. 
</P>
</TEXT>
