<HEADLINE> Mongolian Financial Situation Is Critical: Elbegdorj </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian Prime Minister Tsakhya
Elbegdorj said Saturday that his country's financial situation is
critical.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters one month after he took office, Elbegdorj
said that one of the major causes of the situation is the Asian
financial crisis that impacted adversely on the Mongolian economy.
</P>
<P>
Copper, gold and wool has been the major export commodities of
Mongolia, Elbegdorj said.
</P>
<P>
The price drop of these commodities in the world market has
made Mongolia unable to earn its anticipated income, while cheap
goods from the Asian market has lead to an increase of imports and
a trade deficit, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is formulating a new economic and social
development strategy, which is focusing on increasing income and
practicing frugality.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will take more efforts to reform
customs, finance and accounting, the tax and statistics
departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
