<HEADLINE> Boardman Wins Round Britain Prologue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Chris Boardman regained
his form to win the prologue time trial of the Round Britain
cycling race in Stirling, Scotland, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Boardman, the world one-hour record holder, defeated American
George Hincapie by 1.70 seconds over the 4.2 kilometers course
with a time of six minutes 8.68 seconds and an average speed of
41.01 kph.
</P>
<P>
Poland's Dariusz Baranowski held the lead for more than an hour
before he was overtaken by his U.S. Postal Service team mate
Hincapie. 
