<HEADLINE> A Japanese Movie Confusing Right and Wrong (Part One) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 23 (Xinhua) -- In Japan, once every while, there
usually will be someone coming up to whitewash Japanese war
criminals and its wars of aggression in history. The movie "Pride,
the Fateful Moment," which is now on there, is just another example.
</P>
<P>
The movie, by distorting historic truth, confusing right and
wrong, and boisterously glorifying Hideko Tojo, a class-A war
criminal whose hands dripped with the blood of peoples of Asian
countries, and the Japanese evil war of aggression, is intended to
overturn the verdict of history.
</P>
<P>
To highlight an image of "patriotism and pride" for Tojo is the
first major attempt of the movie script writer and director.
</P>
<P>
According to the script, Tojo, after the defeat of Japan in the
war, keeps his "astonishing" dignity before he is arrested. During
the trials, Tojo, remaining calm and at easy, speaks forcefully
and volubly in self-justification. And when the tribunal's rule is
announced sentencing him and six other war criminals to be hanged,
Tojo "nods twice, and then the third time, seemingly wearing a
smile." As the director's brain product, Tojo appears completely a
hero. Talking to his lawyers, Tojo says, puffed up with pride, "I
was not wrong. What I did was right." "We lost because we didn't
have enough power. But we must keep our nation's honor up."
</P>
<P>
As is known to all, Hideko Tojo, Adolf Hitler and Benito
Mussolini are locked together on the pillory of history as top
fascist criminals of World War II. Historic records show
that Tojo committed too many crimes.
</P>
<P>
As military police chief of the Kanto Army Group, Tojo came to
northeast China to fanatically suppress the anti-Japanese struggle
of the Chinese people. He was later promoted as chief of staff of
the notorious Kanto Army Group.
</P>
<P>
After Japan used the Lugouqiao (or Marco Polo Bridge) Incident
as an excuse to launch an all-out aggression against China, Tojo
led his "Tojo troops" into north China and carried out the policy
of "burning all, killing all and looting all."
</P>
<P>
After becoming the army minister in the Konoe Fumimaro cabinet,
he strongly advocated further escalating the aggression in China
and starting another against the Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
As the Fumimaro cabinet stepped down, Tojo, on the peak of his
power, grabbed the portfolios of prime minister, army minister,
interior minister, military supplies minister and general chief of
staff, to apply an authoritarian rule.
</P>
<P>
In addition to his active role in masterminding and
implementing Japan's policies of aggression against China, he
extended the flames of war from China to the Pacific region and
Southeast Asia to impose sufferings on more countries and more
peoples.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tojo established a Taisei Yusankai to replace the
assembly and to intensify fascist rule in Japan.
</P>
<P>
He saved no efforts to preach the theory of "Great East Asia
Co-Prosperity Sphere," and plotted to set up a "Great East Asia
Province" for plundering more from the occupied territories.
</P>
<P>
After Japan's surrender, Tojo attempted a suicide to escape
punishment, and was hanged on December 23, 1948, by the order of
the International Military Tribunal for the Far East. Even death
could not expiate all his crimes.
</P>
<P>
However, to such an unpardonable war criminal, the movie script
writer and director have shown their special love. Fifty years
after Tojo was sent to the gallows, they, blind to Tojo's
distorted personality as a war maniac and all his crimes, cudgeled
their brains to deliberately depict Tojo as a fearless "hero" with
human touch.
</P>
<P>
Besides reversing the verdict on Tojo, their other objective is
to wake up "self-esteem" in the Japanese people by using Tojo's
"personality" power they have concocted for him, and make people
regard the war as a great pride of the Japanese nation so as to
discard their "self-sadistic conception of history," the admission
of the Japanese war of aggression.
</P>
<P>
The second major attempt of the script writer and the director
is to deny the legitimacy of the Tokyo trial of war criminals.
</P>
<P>
In the movie, they argue in the words of a defense lawyer that
the trial at the International Military Tribunal for the Far East
was wrong, that it was "a trial by the winner of the loser, a
direct trial by the victim of the aggressor, and thus it couldn't
be fair."
</P>
<P>
The movie deliberately ignores the historic facts that the
prosecutors and judges, who represented the world's force of
justice, made convincing arguments against and sharp cross
examinations of the war criminals, and tarnishes the chief judge's
image by depicting him as crude and rude, and sometimes even petty
and weak. On the other hand, Hideko Tojo and other war criminals
in the court appear calm and assured. This portraying, obviously
distorted, has an ulterior motive.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
