<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> A Japanese Movie Confusing Right and Wrong (Part Two) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The trial of Japanese war criminal at the International
Military Tribunal for the Far East was a serious and significant
trial in human history. It was also a tough contest between the
world's just force and the Japanese fascists.
</P>
<P>
The tribunal collected numerous pieces of evidence on the
crimes committed by the suspects, including notes taken at
meetings chaired by the Japanese emperor, and at meetings of the
cabinet and of the five top ministers, secret documents of the
puppet Manchukuo regime and of the Nazi German foreign ministry,
and the testimonies of over 1,000 witnesses, including Aisin
Giorro Pu Yi, puppet emperor of Manchukuo. The tribunal also heard
the testimony of over a thousand witnesses.
</P>
<P>
Although Japan invited "learned and capable" U.S. lawyers to
defend its war criminal suspects during cross examination session,
the prosecutors, with an overwhelming amount of hard evidence on
their side, often rendered criminals and their lawyers speechless.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo trial lasted two years and a half. During this
period, the tribunal held 818 court sessions, where a total of 419
witnesses and 4,300 documents were presented. The notes of the
trial, in English, ran 48,412 pages.
</P>
<P>
It took the tribunal nine days, from November 4 to 12, 1948, to
finish reading its 1,213-page verdict. Tojo, the top criminal, got
the punishment he deserved.
</P>
<P>
Denying the criminal nature of the Japanese war of aggression
is the third major attempt of the movie script writer and director.
</P>
<P>
They propagate that the Great East Asia War is "a self-defense
war from the beginning to the end" and a "holy war" aimed at
"liberating" Asia from the "the White rule."
</P>
<P>
As to Japan's crimes in launching the war, they preach, through
the mouths of Japanese lawyers in the movie, that "the war itself
is legal under international law, and killings in war do not
constitute a crime."
</P>
<P>
"It is a pity that some Japanese troops produced brutal events
in China, but such events have been exaggerated, or even
fabricated," they say, adding that "the Nanjing (Nanking) Massacre
does not exist."
</P>
<P>
The war Japan launched against China and other Asian countries
was aggression -- a conclusion reached long ago by the
international community.
</P>
<P>
It was launched in the 1930s because of the intensification of
Japan's domestic economic and political contradictions and the
radical changes in the international environment.
</P>
<P>
The economic crisis in the capitalist world at that time made
Japanese militarism to quicken its pace to invasion.
</P>
<P>
To rid itself of severe economic and social crisis, Japan
adopted Fascist dictatorship, speeded up militarization of its
national economy, started successive aggressions in order to seize
overseas markets by force, re-divide the world and find ways out
of the crisis through war.
</P>
<P>
With the national policy of establishing a "Great East Asia
Co-Prosperity Sphere," Japan launched the war to set up its East
Asia Empire and exercise colonial rule in the region. The Japanese
aggression brought an unprecedented disaster to the Asian people.
</P>
<P>
In China, the Japanese aggressors committed the most brutal and
ruthless crime in human history, the Nanjing (Nanking) Massacre,
an unparalleled savagery, being a typical example.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese aggression ruined Asia's economy and culture, and
its people were reduced to living in absolute poverty. It took
Asian countries a very long time and painful efforts to heel the
wounds.
</P>
<P>
These are striking evidence of crimes committed by the Japanese
aggressors and there is simply no denying of it.
</P>
<P>
However, instead of admitting the aggressive nature of the war,
the Japanese ultra-rightist force, including the movie producers,
tried every means to whitewash it as a just war for liberation of
the Asian people.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of producing such stuff is to confuse historical
facts and deceive the Japanese people, especially the younger
generation. It cannot but make the Asian people, including the
Japanese people, to sharpen their vigilance.
</P>
<P>
The making of this reactionary movie is not something
accidental. It reflects the ever existence of militarist thinking
in Japan. The ideas expressed in it are not anything new, but
belong to the same category promoted by Japan's post-war
ultra-rightest force.
</P>
<P>
What is worrying after all is that the ultra-rightest force
does still have some following in Japan. Otherwise, this
reactionary movie would not have been screened for the public.
</P>
<P>
It is worth our serious thinking about who is behind the scene
to protect and promote the making of the film.
</P>
<P>
We have also noticed that the movie has been severely
criticized and condemned by individuals with sense of justice,
organizations and media in Japan and the international community.
</P>
<P>
History and reality tell us that anyone who goes against
historical trends are doomed to fail and end up in lifting a rock
to drop it only on his own feet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
