<HEADLINE> Hebei Trade Fair Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 23 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 Hebei Economic and
Trade Fair wound up today in this capital of the north China
province, with 717 direct overseas investment contracts signed
worth some 3.95 billion US dollars, of which 2.15 billion will
come from overseas partners.
</P>
<P>
The light, chemical, medicine, machinery and metallurgical
industries, which are Hebei's pillars, clinched 566 contracts with
a total overseas investment of 1.36 billion US dollars, making up
70.9 percent and 62.9 percent, respectively, of the total figures.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong remained the largest investor, contributing 22.5
percent to the total amount of overseas investment. Investment
from the Republic of Korea and Southeast Asian countries dropped,
while that from Europe and north America rose.
</P>
<P>
There was a notable increase in the number of large projects
and high- and new-technology ones. Some 140 projects had a total
investment of 1.69 billion US dollars, and the number of
high- and new-technology projects reached 301, accounting for 19.5
percent and 42.1 percent, respectively, of the total number of
projects agreed upon at the fair.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 business people from 48 countries and regions came
to the fair, which was the 15th held by the province. Nineteen
percent of the business people came from Southeast and Northeast
Asia, representing a slight fall from the previous fair, while
those from Europe and North America accounted for 32 percent, up
six percentage points over the previous fair.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
