<HEADLINE> Chirac Condemns Child Labor As Modern Form of Slavery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 23 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
condemned child labor as a "modern form of slavery."
</P>
<P>
During a meeting Saturday with 13 former child slaves from
Third World countries on a "World March" to protest child labor,
Chirac said slavery is far from being eliminated.
</P>
<P>
Chanting "Exploitation, No, No, No! Education, Yes, Yes, Yes!"
the members of "World March" arrived in France on Friday and were
received by Prime Minister Lionel Jospin in the southwest port
city of La Rochelle.
</P>
<P>
"We are in the year to commemorate the abolition of
slavery. The truth is that slavery is far from being abolished, it
still exists where children are concerned," said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
"The children have told us with much force and emotion their
own stories. They know of many other similar stories told on the
streets by children living in different cities on different
continents," he said. All his guests had reportedly been subjected
to servitude in their homes.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said the campaign being launched by these children
"should have good results."
</P>
<P>
He also expressed support to the International Labor
Organization to elaborate new laws on banning child labor.
</P>
<P>
"This is new. It is important to abolish the practices which
are absolutely inhumane, scandalous and which no longer fit our
time on the eve of the 21st century," said Chirac. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
