<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Smashes Giant Certificate-Faking Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Police in south China's Guangdong
Province recently smashed a certificate forging factory, arresting
three suspects and seizing 150 forged passports and other phoney
certificates as well as facilities used for forging purposes.
</P>
<P>
A local police officer told a press conference today that the
gang made and sold fake passports and other types of certificates
in Guangdong, Hong Kong and Japan, while organizing illegal
emigration.
</P>
<P>
Police forces in Guangdong, Hong Kong and Japan as well as the
Hong Kong Immigration Department jointly established a group last
year to investigate the case, which took nine months, the officer
said.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigations show that since 1992 the
transnational criminal gang forged more than 1,000 certificates,
including passport of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
and British BNO passports, and sold them overseas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
