<HEADLINE> Writers, Artists to Follow Jiang Zemin's Literature, Art Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Literary and art circles in China
must follow Jiang Zemin's directions on literature and art in
their artistic production and research, a senior culture official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Gao Zhanxiang, vice-chairman of the China Federation of
Literary and Art Circles (CFLAC), made the statement at a
symposium held by the CFLAC and Chinese Writers' Association to
commemorate the 56th anniversary of Mao Zedong's famous speech on
literary and art work in Yan'an in 1942, and the letter Chinese
President Jiang Zemin wrote on May 20, 1995 to 100 Chinese artists
who were to attend a nationwide cultural activity with the theme
of collecting folk arts across the country, which was made public
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The letter calls on Chinese artists to realize the prosperity
of cultural and art creation in accordance to the country's new
situation, Gao said, adding that it also provides basic
policies for current literature and art work.
</P>
<P>
The policies of "going deeper into the masses and grassroots,
and serving the people and socialism," inherit and further develop
Marxist aesthetic principles, as well as Mao Zedong's and Deng
Xiaoping's theories on literature and art, he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four years, Chinese artists have collected
abundant folk art works and have created a lot of good products in
the fields of literature, music, film and painting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
