<HEADLINE> IBF Special Award for Veteran Chinese Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 23 (Xinhua) - The International Badminton
Federation (IFB) honored veteran Chinese coach Wang Wenjiao with a
Distinguished Service Award here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At a special ceremony held prior to the final of the 17th Uber
Cup Finals in Hong Kong's Elizabeth Stadium, 65-year-old Wang, who
retired earlier this week, was presented with the award by IBF
President Lu Shengrong, accompanied by Aeather Niensen, IBF's
Council Member and Chair of the Award Committee.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very happy to receive the Award today. From my 57 years
of service to badminton, I know that it is a sport needing
collective efforts and teamwork. If I have made some contribution
to badminton, I owe it to everyone around me," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Born in Indonesia, Wang went back to China in 1954. He was a
player of China's national team and, after his retirement from
competition, became a national coach and the head coach of the
national team. He served as the president of the Chinese
Badminton Association, vice president of the Asian Badminton
Confederation and a Council Member of the IBF. 
</P>
</TEXT>
