<HEADLINE> UN Car in Angola Attacked, Killing One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 23 (Xinhua) -- A vehicle of the United Nations
Observers Mission in Angola was attacked when driving on a road
in the north province of Malanje Wednesday, resulting in one
killed and three others wounded.
</P>
<P>
A news release available here Saturday said unidentified armed
men mounted an attack on the car at a bridge five km north of
Calandula city in the province, killing an Angolan interpreter.
</P>
<P>
The three injured in the mission were a commander of the
national police in Calandula, a Kenyan army man and a Malian
policeman, and they were all sent to a hospital in Luanda for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
A team comprising U.N. senior officers and policemen went to
the spot in Calandula to probe the event which is one of the
incidents occurring in the north recently.
</P>
<P>
The government has blamed ex-soldiers of the National Union
for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) for the armed raids
on civilian targets, but the U.N. release did not mention UNITA
in the incident so far. 
</P>
