<HEADLINE> Souvenir Cover to Commemorate HKSAR's LegCo Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 23 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Post hosted a
presentation ceremony here Saturday to mark the issue of a
souvenir cover to commemorate the first Legislative Council
Election of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) to
be held on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At the presentation ceremony, both Postmaster General Robert
Footman and Chairman of the Electoral Affairs Commission Justice
Woo Kwok-hing officiated the datestamping of an enlarged souvenir
cover with two meters in length and one in breadth on the stage.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the presentation ceremony, Footman said: "Hong Kong
is entering into a new era as we are electing members of the first
Legislative Council of the HKSAR."
</P>
<P>
He said that the Hong Kong Post is honored to take an active
role in the promotion of the election and has assisted the
candidates for the election to distribute a large volume of
promotional material to over 2.8 million voters in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"We are also spreading the vote on May 24 message all over Hong
Kong by issuing a souvenir cover to commemorate the event," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, the Hong Kong post is offering a unique postmark
hand-back service available Saturday at all post offices. This is
the first time that a postmark will bear two dates of Saturday and
Sunday, he added.
</P>
<P>
The first Legislative Council of the HKSAR will be composed of
60 members with 20 to be returned from the geographical
constituencies, 30 from the functional constituencies and 10 from
the 800-strong Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
During Sunday's election, voters in Hong Kong will cast their
votes to choose from 156 candidates the 50 members of the
Legislative Council and 10 candidates of uncontested functional
constituencies have already been declared elected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
