<HEADLINE> France Sends Experts, Rescue Team to Quake-Striken Bolivia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 23 (Xinhua) -- France is sending three experts to
Bolivia to evaluate the needs of aid after the country was struck
Friday by an earthquake of 6.6 degrees on the Richter scale, said
an official communique here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a 17-member French rescue team consisting of doctors
and searching dogs will arrive in Bolivia on Saturday evening to
help rescue the victims of the earthquake, said the communique
published by the French Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
According to latest reports, 52 people have been killed in the
earthquake which shook the two rural communes of Aiquile and
Totora in central Bolivia on Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
France has 10 air-borne disaster rescue teams which can be
mobilized within three hours and three rapid intervention teams of
doctors. 
</P>
