<HEADLINE> Iranian FM: NAM, OIC Cooperation Important </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi Saturday underlined the importance of cooperation the
Non-Aligned Movement (NAM) and the Organization of the Islamic
Conference (OIC).
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival from the NAM ministerial meeting in Cartagena,
Colombia, Kharrazi said that avenues should be explored and
necessary mechanisms should be devised to make the two bodies more
active, Iranian official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Iran is the current president of the 55-member OIC, and
Colombia, president of the 113-member NAM. The two organizations
of the developing countries share some members and some goals like
economic cooperation and development.
</P>
<P>
He said that he discussed international political and economic
developments as well as promotion of bilateral relations with
Colombian leaders.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that he voiced concern over India's recent
nuclear tests in his talks with the Indian officials on the
sidelines of the meeting, reiterating that Iran favors
non-proliferation and full destruction of nuclear weapons.
</P>
