<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanjing Hosts Symposium on Hong Kong TV Play Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 23 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on TV play series
produced by Hong Kong artists were held from May 20 to 22 in this
capital city of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Over 40 experts and critics from Hong Kong and many inland
areas of China including Beijing and Shanghai reviewed the history
and the future of Hong Kong's TV play series, and discussed the TV
plays' creation, art, social effect, production system, and
broadcasting.
</P>
<P>
The experts watched a number of representatives of Hong Kong TV
play series produced in different periods and agreed that most of
the HK-produced TV series feature patriotism and extol the true,
the good and the beautiful, with modern TV technology designs and
attractive action show.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was sponsored by the China Television Artists
Association and the Jiangsu Television Station.  
</P>
</TEXT>
