to disclose all the facts regarding the nuclear tests and
compensate the people for the damages caused because of the
nuclear tests carried out in 1974 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the Indian government is trying to suppress the data
and factual information regarding the preparation and the tests.
</P>
<P>
The tests have actually resulted in a shift of policy from
India's anti-nuclear policy. The present government's action went
absolutely against the people's fundamental right of to life and
personal liberty guaranteed by the Constitution of India, the
letter said. 
