<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 23 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.7 on
the open-ended Richter scale jolted wide areas from central to
southwestern Japan early Saturday, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties, no
"tsunami" or tidal waves warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 4:49 a.m. (local time), was
centered about 90 kilometers below the seabed in the Iyonada or
the Sea of Iyo inside the Inland Sea.
</P>
<P>
West Japan Railway Co. said that Sanyo Shinkansen bullet trains
were delayed between Hiroshima and Tokuyama, Yamaguchi Prefecture,
and other stations in the region as they had slowed down to await
a damage check. 
