<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba Meets WHO Target on Leprosy Eradication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Cuba has fulfilled the World Health
Organization (WHO) target of eliminating leprosy by the year 2000
and is now in the "post-elimination phase," Cuban Health Ministry
sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The prevalent rate of leprosy in the island country stands as
low as under one per 10,000 inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
Of the 662 existing cases, 85 percent were diagnosed
in a precocious stage of affection and therefore are free of
sequelae, added the sources.
</P>
<P>
The therapeutic plan proposed by the WHO is carried out in Cuba
with highly efficacious medicines that cure leprosy detected at
an early stage of affection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
