<HEADLINE> Indonesia's New Cabinet Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's "Reform Development
Cabinet" was sworn in here Saturday morning at the Presidential
(Merdeka) Palace.
</P>
<P>
The swearing-in ceremony was presided over by new President B.
J. Habibie who took oath on Thursday after former president
Soeharto resigned that day.
</P>
<P>
Habibie, the third president of Indonesia, formed his 36-member
cabinet Friday which included four coordinating ministers, 20
ministers and 12 state ministers.
</P>
<P>
In the new cabinet, 20 ministers are old faces in the Soeharto
cabinet which was formed on March 14 this year.
</P>
<P>
However, for the first time in 30 years, Habibie's new cabinet
included three politicians from the two minority parties, the
United Development Part (PPP) and the Indonesian Democratic Party
(PDI).
</P>
<P>
Habibie also recruited more people from the academia to enter
his cabinet.
</P>
<P>
"We will build a clean and independent government free from
inefficiency, corruption, collusion and nepotism," Habibie said
when announcing the cabinet line-up Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
