<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes over 260 KG of Drugs in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 23 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized over
260 kilograms of narcotic drugs, including 36 kilograms of heroin
and 189 kilograms of opium in April, the official newspaper New
Light of Myanmar reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The seizures, made by army units, police and the Customs
Department, also included 28 litres of phensedyl, 43,378 tablets
of amphetamine stimulant drug.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the country's combined teams destroyed a
total of 0.15 hectare of poppy plantation in Paletwa, Chin State,
and army units destroyed three heroin refinery camps in Muse and
Kutkai townships, Shan State, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The authorities took action against 383 people in connection
with 278 drug-related cases.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the authorities seized 2,400
kilograms of narcotic drugs, including 138 kilograms of heroin,
and destroyed 8,263 hectares of poppy plantations and 8 heroin
refinery camps during the first three months of this year.
</P>
