<HEADLINE> World Bank to Support China's Rural Health Care Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has approved an 85
million US dollars soft loan to support China's rural health
care project.
</P>
<P>
The project, covering more than 40 million people, aims to
improve health conditions and promote the efficiency and
availability of health care services for the poor in China's rural
areas, according to today's People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
The benefited areas are in Henan, Shanxi, Anhui, Qinghai,
Gansu, Guizhou, Shaanxi, and Sichuan provinces and Chongqing
municipality.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project will be 129.2 million US dollars,
of which 44.2 million US dollars will be provided by the Chinese
government.
</P>
<P>
The credit has been designed for two parts, the Basic Health
Services project and the Qinba Health Program, said the World
Bank officials.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank also plans to support the health care in urban
areas through other projects. 
</P>
