<HEADLINE> Indonesian Central Bank Hails Gov't Decision to Make BI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's central bank, Bank
Indonesia (BI), welcomed the decision of the new president to
separate the bank from the new cabinet line-up to assure its
independency.
</P>
<P>
"The independency will make the central bank easier in making
important decisions. It will be easy for BI to make decisions upon
monetary stability and not other considerations," BI Governor
Syahril Sabirin said here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
President Habibie, when announcing the new cabinet Friday
morning, said he had not put he post of central bank governor into
the new cabinet formation as before because he wanted it
independent.
</P>
<P>
Many quarters said one of the factors that had helped cause the
fall of the rupiah (national currency) value so far was BI's
dependency.
</P>
<P>
Under the old system any decisions to be made by BI governor
had to be consulted first with the Minister of Finance and the
Monetary Board.
</P>
<P>
The Bureaucracy has made BI infertile and criticized as having
no sense of crisis.
</P>
<P>
Syahril Sabirin said BI's short-term program would be how to
stabilize the rupiah value.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah value has dropped by about 75 percent or from merely
2,400 against the U.S. dollar in July last to more than 10,000 per
dollar now.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
