<DOCNO> XIE19980523.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> A Woman Dies Every Hour in Peru in Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A woman dies every hour in Peru from
pregnancy complications, during labor, or after delivery.
</P>
<P>
Every year 8,760 women die here for lack of attention during
pregnancy or labor, Miriam Cruz Olave, representative of the
Panamerican Health Organization (PAHO), said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The PAHO official, quoted by the press, said that 265 women die
for every 100,000 children born alive.
</P>
<P>
Also, of the one million pregnancies registered every year in
the country, almost 650,000 end with delivery, and 350,000 as
abortions, most of them induced.
</P>
<P>
She explained that the main causes of death are hemorrhages,
hypertension induced by pregnancy, infections during and after
labor in unsanitary conditions.
</P>
<P>
The PAHO representative also attributed the death to abortion
practised in unsanitary conditions, prolonged delivery obstructed
by narrowness of the pelvis of the mother, or an unusual position
of the baby.
</P>
<P>
The official said that every year 50 million women across the
world suffer complications during pregnancy, delivery, or
postpartum, which causes the death of a woman every minute in the
the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
