-- China's worst forest fire this year was brought under
control yesterday, thanks to the combined efforts of fire-fighters
and natural and artificial precipitation.
</P>
<P>
However, some 60,000 forest wardens who had fought the fire
since May 13 were still patrolling the forest in eastern Inner
Mongolia for any sign of flames being rekindled by the strong
winds.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China yesterday denied as absurd US allegations that certain
American satellite manufacturers had leaked missile technology to
China.
</P>
<P>
According to the allegations, two US companies, Space
Systems/Loral and Hughes Space and Communications, provided
missile technology to China during an accident assessment in 1996
after a Long March 3B vehicle failed to launch the Intelsat 708
into orbit.
</P>
<P>
