<HEADLINE> China's Large TV Producer to Merge Two Factories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 23 (Xinhua) -- Changhong Electronics Group, one of
China's largest TV producers, is seeking the merger of two
television set factories in east China's Fujian province.
</P>
<P>
The firm is now negotiating with Hitachi Fujian in Fuzhou,
capital of Fujian, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The plan for Hitachi Fujian's acquisition is Changhong's second
endeavour in the province. Changhong's President Ni Runfeng
visited Xiamen on May 3 for the possible acquisition of Xiahua,
another TV maker in the province.
</P>
<P>
Changhong, formerly a manufacturer of goods for the military,
is now producing goods for civil use, such as TV sets, air
conditioners, and other electronic products.
</P>
<P>
Last year, its production was valued at 25.65 billion yuan,
accounting for 35 percent of China's color TV market.
</P>
<P>
This year, it plans to make nine million color TV sets and have
40 percent of the market.
</P>
<P>
Hitachi Fujian is one of the earliest TV producers in China to
use Japanese technology. However, it has been in difficulty in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Xiahua, a company listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange,
reported 1.34 billion yuan in revenue from core business last
year, up 37.59 percent over 1996. However, its net profits
registered only a feeble 4.63 percent rise.  
</P>
</TEXT>
