<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, May 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Floods caused by heavy rains in Turkey's western
Black Sea region have cut off power and telephone lines, swept
away roads and damaged buildings, virtually paralyzing these areas.
</P>
<P>
At least 12 people have reportedly been killed and 13 others
went missing in flood-hit areas. The main road to Zonguldak
province from the capital Ankara, some 300 kilometers in length,
was ruined by fast-running river water that overflowed.
(Turkey-Floods)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami Friday expressed
concern about India's nuclear tests and urged Pakistan to exercise
patience and self-restraint over the issue.
</P>
