<P>
NAIROBI -- At least 17 passengers were killed and hundreds
injured in a tragic train accident Friday morning in Malawi's
southern Thyolo District, about 40 km east of Blantyre.
</P>
<P>
The train which left Blantyre's Limbe station at 5 a.m.
derailed due to "a faulty breaking system" as it negotiated a bend
at Lunda on its way to a southern-most Nsanje District close to
Mozambican border. (Malawi-Train Accident)
</P>
