WASHINGTON -- President Bill Clinton on Friday repeated his
accusation of India for its nuclear tests, which he said threatens
the stability in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the U.S. Naval Academy, Clinton said India's
nuclear tests raised the "specter of a dangerous rivalry" in the
region. (US-India-Clinton)
</P>
