WASHINGTON -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright said Friday
that the United States would assist Indonesia for a peaceful
transition to democracy.
</P>
<P>
"Indonesia's course will be determined by Indonesians alone,"
Albright said in an address at the University of Maryland. "But
the United States will continue to do what it can to assist those
within Indonesia who are working for democracy, tolerance and
law." (US-Indonesia-Albright)
</P>
