<HEADLINE> Chile, Spain to Promote Cooperation in Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Chile and Spain have agreed to
increase their consultations in the area of defense policies aimed
at strengthening bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A Chilean Defense Ministry communique released Friday said that
Defense Minister Raul Troncoso and his Spanish counterpart Eduardo
Serra were satisfied with the Chilean-Spanish relations in this
field.
</P>
<P>
Such relations, the communique said, have developed adequately
since the signing of the protocol of cooperation between both
ministries in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The document also said that the two ministries examined a wide
range of matters of mutual interest, and exchanged information and
opinions about the development of their respective defense
policies.
</P>
<P>
They gave special importance to the continuation of exchanges
of delegations and meetings of groups of experts with the purpose
of expanding the communications between the defense communities of
the two countries, added the communique. 
