<HEADLINE> Dutch Men Take Second Game in Hockey Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Hosts the Netherlands routed India
with five unanswered goals on Friday to take their second win at
the World Cup Field Hockey Tournament in Utrecht.
</P>
<P>
All five goals were scored off field with captain Stephan Veen
contributing three of them, two in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Teun de Nooijer and Remco van Wijk each added one to complete
the scoring spree for the Olympic champions.
</P>
<P>
Germany also scored its second win by blanking New Zealand 3-0
while Canada and South Korea fought to a 1-1 draw, the first in
the three-day-old tourney.
</P>
<P>
In women's action of the day, Olympic and World Cup titlists
Australia proved their form and flair in the game by trouncing
China 7-1.
</P>
<P>
The German women also strengthened their position for
advancement by beating South Africa 4-3.
</P>
<P>
The United States, that went 5-1 down to Germany in the opening
day, got one win back as it overwhelmed Scotland 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Twelve teams are competing in each of the men's and women's
tournament with only the top two teams from round-robin group
preliminaries scheduled to enter the medal round starting next
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
