<HEADLINE> OAU Stresses Peace Solution to Ethio-Eritrean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
Secretary-General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
said Friday that only a peaceful resolution of the border dispute
between Ethiopia and Eritrea based on dialogue and negotiation
can be a real solution.
</P>
<P>
In his message on the occasion cerebrating the 35th birthday
of the OAU, Salim said that "the on-going crisis between Ethiopia
and Eritrea is a matter of grave concern to us."
</P>
<P>
Salim pointed out that the dispute "constitutes a setback to
the commendable efforts made by the leaders of the two countries,
and to the other leaders in the region, to bring about peace,
security, stability and development."
</P>
<P>
He said that "it is my earnest hope that wisdom will prevail
and that both parties will do their utmost to avoid an escalation
of the crisis and to seek a peaceful solution to it."
</P>
<P>
"The alternative of escalation can only spell disaster for the
peoples of Ethiopia and Eritrea as well as for the region as a
whole," Salim said, adding that "Africa, which has been
strengthened by the stability and understanding and cooperation
between these two sister states can only be seriously undermined
if the crisis is allowed to escalate."
</P>
<P>
"It is, therefore, in our collective interest to spare no
effort to find a peaceful solution to this unfortunate dispute,"
Salim added.
</P>
<P>
It is recalled that on May 18, Salim strongly appealed to the
leadership of Ethiopia and Eritrea to seek a peaceful solution to
the crisis and to do their utmost to avoid a further escalation
of the crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
