<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Conference on Eco-Society to Be Held in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The World Conference on
International Cooperation of Cities and Citizens for Cultivating
an Eco-Society, known as "Eco-Partnership Tokyo", will be held in
Tokyo from May 26-29, the United Nations announced today.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the conference under the auspices of the U.N.
and the Tokyo Metropolitan Government is to provide a forum for
representatives from the world cities and citizens to clarify and
strengthen partnerships to create an eco-society.
</P>
<P>
Eco-society is defined for this conference as a society that
pursues the adapting of human activities to the natural cycles of
the environment.
</P>
<P>
Believed to be the first large conference recently convened
jointly by the U.N. and a local government to deal with urban
problems and challenges critical to the quality of life, it is
expected to draw about 1000 delegates.
</P>
<P>
The meeting intends to focus on three major themes, including
the establishment of regional recycling systems, international
cooperation towards an eco-society and new patterns of consumption
and production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
